<TITLE>Be like Jesus, dont resist arrest, Christian tells Apostle Suleman</TITLE>


<TEXT>
A Nigerian Christian has a message for Apostle Johnson Suleman of Omega Fire Ministry. 
 
Suleman will <EVENT eid="e1" class="OCCURRENCE">appear</EVENT> before DSS on <TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DATE" value="2017-01-23">Monday</TIMEX3> over his comments on murderous Fulani herdsmen. 
 
He had <EVENT eid="e2" class="REPORTING">told</EVENT> his church security personnel to <EVENT eid="e3" class="OCCURRENCE">kill</EVENT> and <EVENT eid="e4" class="OCCURRENCE">behead</EVENT> any herdsman who enters here by mistake. Suleman <EVENT eid="e5" class="REPORTING">said</EVENT> he will not <EVENT eid="e6" class="OCCURRENCE">apologise</EVENT> for the comments because they were <EVENT eid="e7" class="OCCURRENCE">directed</EVENT> to murderous herdsmen. 
 
The DSS <EVENT eid="e8" class="I_ACTION">tried</EVENT> to <EVENT eid="e9" class="OCCURRENCE">arrest</EVENT> him but he <EVENT eid="e10" class="OCCURRENCE">resisted</EVENT> with the help of Ekiti governor Ayodele Fayose. 
 
DSS later <EVENT eid="e11" class="OCCURRENCE">invited</EVENT> Suleman for a chat. He will <EVENT eid="e12" class="OCCURRENCE">appear</EVENT> before the secret service on <TIMEX3 tid="t2" type="DATE" value="2017-01-23">Monday</TIMEX3>. 
 
Some Christians <EVENT eid="e13" class="REPORTING">say</EVENT> they <EVENT eid="e14" class="I_STATE">want</EVENT> to <EVENT eid="e15" class="OCCURRENCE">march</EVENT> for the man of God but Godswill Jumbo thinks people are <EVENT eid="e16" class="OCCURRENCE">missing</EVENT> the point. 
 
The Christian faith cannot be <EVENT eid="e17" class="OCCURRENCE">defended</EVENT> by any world government, political establishment or even civil society. It defends itself amidst the fires of persecution, Jumbo <EVENT eid="e18" class="REPORTING">wrote</EVENT>. 
 
If a pastor or Christian feels he is being <EVENT eid="e19" class="OCCURRENCE">persecuted</EVENT>, let him <EVENT eid="e20" class="OCCURRENCE">follow</EVENT> the footsteps of our Lord Jesus Christnon-resistance, non-retaliation. 
 
Christianity is <EVENT eid="e21" class="OCCURRENCE">fueled</EVENT> by holy passion <EVENT eid="e22" class="OCCURRENCE">generated</EVENT> in the heart of the <EVENT eid="e23" class="OCCURRENCE">believer</EVENT> by the Holy Spirit not by politics. We are not <EVENT eid="e24" class="OCCURRENCE">called</EVENT> to <EVENT eid="e25" class="OCCURRENCE">retaliate</EVENT> or even self defense. We are also not <EVENT eid="e26" class="OCCURRENCE">called</EVENT> to civil disobedience except where asked to <EVENT eid="e27" class="OCCURRENCE">recant</EVENT> our faith. 
 
When Jesus was <EVENT eid="e28" class="OCCURRENCE">arrested</EVENT> by Roman soldiers He never <EVENT eid="e29" class="REPORTING">resisted</EVENT>. Before Caiaphas, the high priest and Pilate the Roman governor he <EVENT eid="e30" class="I_ACTION">refused</EVENT> to <EVENT eid="e31" class="OCCURRENCE">defend</EVENT> himself in the face of false accusations. He willingly <EVENT eid="e32" class="OCCURRENCE">offered</EVENT> to be <EVENT eid="e33" class="OCCURRENCE">condemned</EVENT>, tortured and <EVENT eid="e34" class="OCCURRENCE">crucified</EVENT>. He even <EVENT eid="e35" class="I_ACTION">prayed</EVENT> for his persecutors <EVENT eid="e36" class="OCCURRENCE">cum</EVENT> oppressors. Thats the way to <EVENT eid="e37" class="OCCURRENCE">go</EVENT> for every Christian. Not the other way around. Let no one attempt to <EVENT eid="e38" class="OCCURRENCE">change</EVENT> the Christian narrative. 
 
Every Christian should be like Christ! 
    Author: Rotimi Akinola  
I love to have unfettered conversations about the media, religion, education, human rights, politics and everything in between. Aside creating web content, I also <EVENT eid="e39" class="I_STATE">cherish causing</EVENT> the world some trouble as I, despite a looming global water crisis, <EVENT eid="e40" class="OCCURRENCE">drink</EVENT> three litres of the liquid on a daily basis thereby <EVENT eid="e41" class="OCCURRENCE">shortening</EVENT> the ration of the rest of humanity. 
